Police officers from Port Shepstone Search and Rescue and K9 Search and Rescue units made the gruesome discovery of a foetus buried in a shallow grave in Umzumbe on Monday. Captain Nqobile Gwala, KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said that the SAPS members were responding to the possible concealment of birth complaint when they made the discovery. Gwala said: “K9 Bear was utilised at an area pointed out by an eyewitness and after a positive reaction, the area was carefully dug open. A foetus wrapped in a linen saver was found in the shallow grave. The foetus was placed in a small body bag and handed over to forensic pathology services on scene and all role players in attendance.” A concealment of birth docket was opened at Hibberdene SAPS.